The paper deals with lightweight description logics and their extensions, which are commonly studied in the areas of logic, artificial intelligence, and databases. The paper also discusses decision procedures for subsumption testing and interpolation, which are important topics in automated reasoning and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
